               <p>MR. COOPER conducted the prosecution.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280221-263-person1494">
                  THOMAS 
                  GREENFIELD
               <interp inst="t18280221-263-person1494" type="surname" value="GREENFIELD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-263-person1494" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280221-263-person1494" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am coachman to Mrs. Deborah Dixon, widow; I drove the Henley coach for her from there to London. On the 3d of November, I stopped with the coach at some private stables at <placeName id="t18280221-263-crimeloc1395">Hounslow</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-263-crimeloc1395" type="placeName" value="Hounslow"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280221-263-crimeloc1395" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280221-263-off1392 t18280221-263-crimeloc1395"></join>, which she rents of Stuckbury; before I changed horses I saw the prisoner at the back of the stable; I got off my coach, and went round to the back stable - I had seen the prisoner there before, and desired him not to remain there - it is a private yard: we have two rest-horses and a corn-bin in the back stable; I saw the prisoner go to the bin, and fill a bag, which he hid under the dunghill - he did not see me; I went up, and said, "Mr. Ward, what have you got there?" he said, "D - n it, here is a great rat;" he took up a brick, and ran round the stable; I went after him, but he crossed the field, and ran away; I went to the dung-heap, and found this corn in the bag - it is called horse-corn; all the corn there belongs to Mrs. Dixon - here is nearly a bushel of it.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was never in the stable; I found it under the granary, and threw it on the ground.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280221-263-verdict1396" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280221-263-verdict1396" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 25.</p>
